6. Notion — Create Page (Parent: Database)
Database ID: paste the 32-character ID → ensure the database is shared with the integration.
Property mapping (adjust to your Notion column names):
Title (Title) ← ={{ $json.title }}
Summary (Rich text) ← ={{ $json.snippet }}
Tags (Multi-select) ← (optional, array of strings)
Source (URL) ← ={{ $json.sourceUrl }}
From (Text/Email) ← ={{ $json.fromAddress }}
Date (Date) ← ={{ $json.sentAt }}
Slug (Text) ← ={{ $json.slug }}
Notes (Rich text/Long text, optional) ← ={{ $json.bodyText }}

